defs.docs: `Future`-powered I/O at the core of Tokio

defs.name: IoFuture
defs.docs: A convenience typedef around a `Future` whose error component is `io::Error`

defs.name: IoStream
defs.docs: A convenience typedef around a `Stream` whose error component is `io::Error`

defs.docs: A future which will copy all data from a reader into a writer.

Creates a future which represents copying all the bytes from one object to
 another.

defs.name: EasyBuf
defs.docs: A reference counted buffer of bytes.

defs.name: EasyBufMut
defs.docs:
An RAII object returned from `get_mut` which provides mutable access to the
 underlying `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: Codec
defs.docs: Encoding and decoding of frames via buffers.

defs.name: In
defs.docs: The type of decoded frames.

defs.name: Out
defs.docs: The type of frames to be encoded.

defs.docs: Encoding and decoding of frames via buffers.

defs.name: decode_eof
defs.docs: Encoding and decoding of frames via buffers.

defs.name: encode
defs.value: fn (&mut self, msg: Self::Out, buf: &mut Vec<u8>) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs: Encoding and decoding of frames via buffers.

defs.name: Framed
defs.docs:
A unified `Stream` and `Sink` interface to an underlying `Io` object, using
 the `Codec` trait to encode and decode frames.

defs.name: Flush
defs.docs: A future used to fully flush an I/O object.

defs.name: flush
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will entirely flush an I/O object and then yield the
 object itself.

defs.name: ReadExact
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read exactly enough bytes to fill
 a buffer.

defs.name: read_exact
defs.value: fn <A, T> (a: A, buf: T) -> ReadExact<A, T>
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read exactly enough bytes to fill `buf`,
 returning an error if EOF is hit sooner.

defs.name: ReadToEnd
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read the entire contents of a stream
 into a vector.

defs.name: read_to_end
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read all the bytes associated with the I/O
 object `A` into the buffer provided.

defs.name: read
defs.value: fn <R, T> (rd: R, buf: T) -> Read<R, T>
defs.docs:
Tries to read some bytes directly into the given `buf` in asynchronous
 manner, returning a future type.

defs.name: Read
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read available number of bytes to fill
 a buffer.

defs.name: ReadUntil
defs.docs:
A future which can be used to easily read the contents of a stream into a 
 vector until the delimiter is reached.

defs.name: read_until
defs.value: fn <A> (a: A, byte: u8, buf: Vec<u8>) -> ReadUntil<A>
defs.docs:
Creates a future which will read all the bytes associated with the I/O
 object `A` into the buffer provided until the delimiter `byte` is reached.
 This method is the async equivalent to [`BufRead::read_until`].

defs.name: ReadHalf
defs.docs: The readable half of an object returned from `Io::split`.

defs.name: WriteHalf
defs.docs: The writable half of an object returned from `Io::split`.

defs.name: Window
defs.docs: A owned window around an underlying buffer.

defs.name: WriteAll
defs.docs: A future used to write the entire contents of some data to a stream.

defs.name: write_all
defs.value: fn <A, T> (a: A, buf: T) -> WriteAll<A, T>
defs.docs:
Creates a future that will write the entire contents of the buffer `buf` to
 the stream `a` provided.
